Surgery of small hepatocellular carcinoma. Analysis of 144 cases. A long-term follow-up study of 144 cases with surgically and pathologically proved small hepatocellular carcinoma (less than or equal to 5 cm) from 1967 to 1987 is reported. One hundred eight cases (75.0%) were detected by alpha-fetoprotein serosurvey and/or ultrasonography mainly in a high-risk population 129 cases (89.6%) coexisted with cirrhosis. Resection was done in 132 cases (91.7%) with three (2.3%) operative deaths